<subSubSection lastPageId="59" lastPageNumber="60" pageId="58" pageNumber="59" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="58.[707,1193,1655,1730]" lastBlockId="59.[151,638,194,375]" lastPageId="59" lastPageNumber="60" pageId="58" pageNumber="59">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[731,836,1655,1676]" pageId="58" pageNumber="59">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
The single member of the 
<taxonomicName box="[1115,1193,1655,1676]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Sagola" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="58" pageNumber="59" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lescheni">
<emphasis box="[1115,1193,1655,1676]" italics="true" pageId="58" pageNumber="59">lescheni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species-group can be distinguished from other 
<taxonomicName box="[707,771,1709,1730]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Sagola" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="58" pageNumber="59" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[707,771,1709,1730]" italics="true" pageId="58" pageNumber="59">Sagola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species-groups by the following combination of characters: small body, length 
<quantity box="[505,634,194,216]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.7999999999999998" metricValueMax="1.9" metricValueMin="1.7" pageId="59" pageNumber="60" unit="mm" value="1.7999999999999998" valueMax="1.9" valueMin="1.7">1.7–1.9 mm</quantity>
; antennomere 1 approximately 2 times longer than wide; frontal rostrum prominent (
<figureCitation box="[487,573,247,268]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="59.[175,207,1662,1681]" captionTargetBox="[162,637,1194,1640]" captionTargetId="figure-602@59.[151,637,1189,1647]" captionTargetPageId="59" captionText="Fig. 33. Sagola lescheni (lescheni species-group). a) Habitus, dorsal view; scale bar = 1 mm, b) Aedeagus, dorsal view; scale bar = 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4907829" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4907829/files/figure.png" pageId="59" pageNumber="60">Fig. 33a</figureCitation>
); hind wings well-developed; abdominal tergites IV–VI with discal carinae; broad and flattened genitalia (
<figureCitation box="[158,242,327,348]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="59.[175,207,1662,1681]" captionTargetBox="[162,637,1194,1640]" captionTargetId="figure-602@59.[151,637,1189,1647]" captionTargetPageId="59" captionText="Fig. 33. Sagola lescheni (lescheni species-group). a) Habitus, dorsal view; scale bar = 1 mm, b) Aedeagus, dorsal view; scale bar = 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4907829" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4907829/files/figure.png" pageId="59" pageNumber="60">Fig. 33b</figureCitation>
); only known from 
<collectingRegion box="[445,543,327,348]" country="New Zealand" name="Northland" pageId="59" pageNumber="60">Northland</collectingRegion>
of North Island (
<figureCitation box="[229,306,354,375]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="63.[175,207,1662,1681]" captionTargetBox="[154,636,943,1636]" captionTargetId="figure-502@63.[151,637,938,1639]" captionTargetPageId="63" captionText="Fig. 36. Known collection localities of New Zealand Sagola species. S. lescheni: black circles; S. gourlayi: triangles; S. sharpi: black squares." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4907835" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4907835/files/figure.png" pageId="59" pageNumber="60">Fig. 36</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
